<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?><?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="..\config8\suzuki.xsl" ?><!DOCTYPE suzuki [<!ENTITY % sdatacharaents SYSTEM "..\config8\sdatacharaents.txt">%sdatacharaents;]><suzuki><manual>
<section sectnbr = "2B">
<servcat sctnbr = "02" scnbr = "02">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENAP70A2206003" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Front Strut Assembly Removal and Installation
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70A2206002">Front Strut Assembly Components</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
When rebound stopper and front strut assembly are removed, check that strut support lower nut is tightened to specified torque before installing strut assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70A2206004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Strut bracket nut is precoated with friction stabilizer. Do not reuse nut, otherwise nut may loosen.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention2>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70A2206003001">
<title>
Removal
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove strut rod cap.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
When servicing strut assembly components, loosen strut support upper nut a little before removing strut assembly. This will facilitate service work. Note that the nut must not be removed at this point.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Hoist vehicle, allowing front suspension to be free of vehicle weight.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove front wheel. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70A2406001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove stabilizer joint nut while holding stud using hexagon wrench (2) and then disconnect stabilizer upper joint (1) from strut (3).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A220004.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "52.507mm" ver = "01" gw = "149" gh = "132"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove brake hose mounting bolt (1), to detach brake hose (2), front wheel speed sensor harness (3) and clip (7) from front strut (4) as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove strut bracket nuts (5) and bolts (6).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A220005.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "76.387mm" ver = "01" gw = "236" gh = "200"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove strut support upper nut (1) and rebound stopper (2), then remove front strut assembly from vehicle.
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Hold strut with hands to prevent it from falling off.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A220006.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "42.532mm" ver = "01" gw = "125" gh = "104"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70A2206003002">
<title>
Installation
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70A2206005">Front Strut Inspection</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Reverse removal procedure, noting the following points.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Insert strut bracket bolts (1) in the direction shown in figure.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Use new strut bracket nuts (4).
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Tighten all fasteners to specified torque.
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T2B001">
<t-part>
Strut bracket nut
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
90
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
9.2
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
66.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
<torqueitem id = "T2B002">
<t-part>
Brake hose mounting bolt
</t-part>
<t-part1>
c
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
26
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
2.7
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
19.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
<torqueitem id = "T2B003">
<t-part>
Stabilizer joint nut
</t-part>
<t-part1>
d
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
50
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
5.1
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
37.0
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not twist brake hose and front wheel speed sensor harness when installing them.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Install front wheel speed sensor harness by fitting its grommet (3) on hook of bracket (2).
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Tighten wheel nuts to specified torque. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70A2406001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Lower hoist with vehicle in unloaded condition, then tighten strut support upper nut to specified torque.
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T2B004">
<t-part>
Strut support upper nut
</t-part>
<t-part1>
b
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
50
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
5.1
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
37.0
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A220007.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "109.976mm" ver = "02" gw = "197" gh = "295"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.968in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[f]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Forward
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
After completing installation, check front wheel alignment. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70A2206001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
